9 11:44:19 -0800  233)  * @goals:\t\tHead of quota tuning goals (&damos_quota_goal) list.\nfb12e27081eb8 (SeongJae Park      2026-03-09 18:05:17 -0700  234)  * @goal_tuner:\t\tGoal-based @esz tuning algorithm to use.\n4d791a0a2ab47 (SeongJae Park      2024-02-19 11:44:17 -0800  235)  * @esz:\t\tEffective size quota in bytes.\n2b8a248d58733 (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:16 -0700  236)  *\n38683e003153f (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:33 -0700  237)  * @weight_sz:\t\tWeight of the region's size for prioritization.\n38683e003153f (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:33 -0700  238)  * @weight_nr_accesses:\tWeight of the region's nr_accesses for prioritization.\n38683e003153f (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:33 -0700  239)  * @weight_age:\t\tWeight of the region's age for prioritization.\n38683e003153f (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:33 -0700  240)  *\n2b8a248d58733 (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:16 -0700  241)  * To avoid consuming too much CPU time or IO resources for applying the\n1cd2430300594 (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:23 -0700  242)  * &struct damos->action to large memory, DAMON allows users to set time and/or\n1cd2430300594 (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:23 -0700  243)  * size quotas.  The quotas can be set by writing non-zero values to &ms and\n1cd2430300594 (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:23 -0700  244)  * &sz, respectively.  If the time quota is set, DAMON tries to use only up to\n1cd2430300594 (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:23 -0700  245)  * &ms milliseconds within &reset_interval for applying the action.  If the\n1cd2430300594 (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:23 -0700  246)  * size quota is set, DAMON tries to apply the action only up to &sz bytes\n1cd2430300594 (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:23 -0700  247)  * within &reset_interval.\n1cd2430300594 (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:23 -0700  248)  *\nd783cc5913f17 (SeongJae Park      2025-01-10 10:52:32 -0800  249)  * To convince the different types of quotas and goals, DAMON internally\nd783cc5913f17 (SeongJae Park      2025-01-10 10:52:32 -0800  250)  * converts those into one single size quota called \"effective quota\".  DAMON\nd783cc5913f17 (SeongJae Park      2025-01-10 10:52:32 -0800  251)  * internally uses it as the only one real quota.  The conversion is made as\nd783cc5913f17 (SeongJae Park      2025-01-10 10:52:32 -0800  252)  * follows.\n38683e003153f (SeongJae Park      2021-11-05 13:47:33 -0700  253)  *\nd783cc5913f17 (SeongJae Park      2025-01-10 10:52:32 -0800  254)  * The time quota is transformed to a size quota using estimated throughput of\nd783cc5913f17 (SeongJae Park      2025-01-10 10:52:32 -0800  255)  * the scheme's action.  DAMON then compares it against &sz and uses smaller\nd783cc5913f17 (SeongJae Park      2025-01-10 10:52:32 -0800  256)  * one as the effective quota.\nd783cc5913f17 (SeongJae Park      2025-01-10 10:52:32 -0800  257)  *\nd783cc5913f17 (SeongJae Park      2025-01-10 10:52:32 -0800  258)  * If @goals is not empty, DAMON calculates yet another size quota based on the\n89d347a545a70 (SeongJae Park      2024-02-19 11:44:21 -0800  259)  * goals using its internal feedback loop algorithm, for every @reset_interval.\n89d347a545a70 (SeongJae Park      2024-02-19 11:44:21 -0800  260)  * Then, if the new size quota is smaller than the effective quota, it uses the\n89d347a545a70 (SeongJae Park      2024-02-19 11:44:21 -0800  261)  * new size quota as the effective quota.\n91f21216a79d0 (SeongJae Park      2024-02-19 11:44:19 -0800  262)  *\n78f2f60377ee4 (SeongJae Park      2024-02-19 11:44:12 -0800  263)  * The resulting effective size quota in bytes is set to @esz.\n4d791a0a2ab47 (SeongJae Park      2024-02-19 11:44:17 -0800  264)  *\n4d791a0a2ab47 (SeongJae Park      2024-02-19 11:44:17 -0800  265)  * For selecting regions within the quota, DAMON prioritizes current scheme's\n4d791a0a2ab47 (SeongJae Park      2024-02-19 11:44:17 -0800  266)  * target memory regions