However, further analysis reveals that this isn't a *memory corruption*.  The worst case scenario would be a spurious `-EBUSY` error return from `damos_walk` if the `kdamond` thread is preempted.  `damos_walk` would read the non-`NULL` `ctx->walk_control` value and safely return `-EBUSY`.

However, what if `damos_walk_cancel` runs concurrently with `damos_walk_complete`? Both are on the same thread so this is impossible.

I check if any *other* threads modify `ctx->walk_control`, the only other one is `damos_walk`.

